8-year-old Reagen Gertse will be buried today. He was raped and murdered by a parolee and family member last weekend. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eight-year-old Reagan Gertse has been laid to rest in Tulbagh. The young boy's body was found in a stream behind a factory outside the town last Sunday. READ: Crowd tries to attack alleged child killer Reagan was raped before he was murdered, allegedly by a member of his family who was on parole for another crime. Justice Minister Ronald Lamola has called the efficacy of the parole board into question after multiple violent crimes in the Western Cape. He highlighted that victims are not always considered when offenders are given parole. READ: Boy, 8, allegedly murdered by parolee In another case, the man accused of murdering Tazne van Wyk was also on parole. Reagan's funeral was held at the Chris Hani informal settlement in Tulbagh.